Kafka:

Distirbuted message queue
Horizontally scalable, fault-tolerant
Durable
Fast  
  100 MB reads and writes  per second
  Thousand of clients per broker
  
Defination:
Message : an immutable array of bytes
Topic : a feed of messages
Producer : a process that publishs message to a topic
Consumer: a single-threaded process that subscribes to a topic
Broker : one of the servers that comprise a cluster


Topic Partitioning : 
  0
  1
  2
